        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Formula Shortage Reporting Act of 2022</b></p> <p>This bill requires manufacturers of infant formula to notify the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) at least 72 hours in advance of a manufacturing interruption or product discontinuance that is expected to meaningfully disrupt the product's supply. The FDA must post such information on its website and notify health care providers.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
